definitions.definition: The contents of an automobile (passengers, supplies, etc.) for one trip.
examples: I brought a carload of flowers to her.
We brought a carload of kids and camping gear on our road trip out west.

definitions.definition: The quantity of goods that can be carried in a freight car .
examples: By 1887 the company had grown so large that it was buying its flour and sugar by the carload .

main_definition: The contents of an automobile (passengers, supplies, etc.) for one trip.
secondary_definitions: ( rail transport , US , Canada ) The quantity of goods that can be carried in a freight car .
